OL,5, Nearly 180,000 children in England who 
OL,6, care for a relative may be missing out 
OL,7, on support because they are not known  
OL,8, to their council, BBC News analysis    
OL,9, suggests.                              
OL,11,FLocal authorities have a duty to       
OL,12,Fidentify, assess and support children  
OL,13,Fwho provide a caring role.             
OL,15,FBut experts say many are not getting   
OL,16,Fthe help and time off they need.       
OL,18,FMinisters said councils had a duty to  
OL,19,Fsupport carers but the Local Government
OL,20,FAssociation called for better funding. 
